title: Wall Elevation Design, probably for the King's Apartments, Royal Pavilion, Brighton
medium: Brush and watercolor, white gouache, graphite on paper
description:
Elevation of a wall with a doorway at right, surmounted by a painted tablet bearing Chinese characters. The decoration of the wall at left consists of a Chinese scene within a circular frame, flanked by narrow panels with neutral fields.

Original album associated with this collection still exists: see 1948-40-1 accessory.
name: Drawing
